## Why Business Model Matters

Different business models have fundamentally different funnels, metrics, and attribution needs:

| Business Model | Primary Metric | Funnel Complexity | Key Challenge |
|---------------|----------------|-------------------|---------------|
| **SaaS** | MRR/ARR | Medium (trial-based) | Activation + retention |
| **E-commerce** | Revenue/AOV | Simple (purchase-based) | Repeat purchases |
| **Marketplace** | GMV | High (dual-sided) | Balancing supply + demand |
| **B2B Lead Gen** | Pipeline/Closed Won | Complex (sales-assisted) | Long cycles, handoffs |

Using the wrong template leads to:
- Misaligned funnel stages
- Wrong conversion rate expectations
- Inappropriate attribution models
- Inaccurate forecasts

## Template 1: SaaS (Subscription Software)

### Funnel Structure

```
SaaS Funnel
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

Stage 1: VISITOR (ToFU)
├── Definition: First website visit
├── Attribution: First-touch
└── Key metric: Unique visitors by channel

        ↓ [Signup Rate: 2-5%]

Stage 2: SIGNUP / FREE TRIAL (MoFU)
├── Definition: Creates account or starts trial
├── Attribution: Linear (multiple touches drive signup)
└── Key metric: Trial starts, signups by channel

        ↓ [Activation Rate: 30-60%]

Stage 3: ACTIVATED USER (MoFU)
├── Definition: Completes key activation milestone
├── Attribution: Participation (which channels touched activated users)
└── Key metric: Activated trials by source channel

        ↓ [Conversion Rate: 15-40%]

Stage 4: PAID CUSTOMER (BoFU)
├── Definition: Starts paid subscription
├── Attribution: Last-touch (closing channel)
└── Key metric: New MRR by channel
```

### SaaS Metrics to Track

| Metric | Definition | Attribution Model |
|--------|------------|-------------------|
| **CAC by channel** | Cost per acquired customer | Full-funnel weighted |
| **Trial-to-Paid** | % of trials converting | Last-touch |
| **Activation rate** | % completing key milestone | Participation |
| **LTV:CAC ratio** | Lifetime value vs acquisition cost | First-touch (sourcing) |
| **Payback period** | Months to recover CAC | First-touch |

### SaaS Forecast Formula

```ruby
# SaaS Monthly Revenue Forecast
def saas_monthly_forecast(channel)
  visitors = project_visitors(channel)               # From ToFU
  signups = visitors * signup_rate(channel)          # 2-5%
  activated = signups * activation_rate(channel)     # 30-60%
  converted = activated * conversion_rate(channel)   # 15-40%
  new_mrr = converted * average_plan_value           # New MRR

  # Add expansion and subtract churn for total MRR
  total_mrr = existing_mrr + new_mrr + expansion_mrr - churned_mrr

  {
    new_customers: converted,
    new_mrr: new_mrr,
    total_mrr: total_mrr
  }
end
```

### SaaS Benchmark Rates

| Stage Transition | Low | Median | High |
|-----------------|-----|--------|------|
| Visitor → Signup | 1% | 3% | 8% |
| Signup → Activated | 20% | 40% | 70% |
| Activated → Paid | 10% | 25% | 50% |
| **Overall Visitor → Paid** | 0.02% | 0.3% | 2.8% |

