## Template 2: E-commerce (Direct Product Sales)

### Funnel Structure

```
E-commerce Funnel
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

Stage 1: VISITOR (ToFU)
├── Definition: First product page view
├── Attribution: First-touch
└── Key metric: Sessions by channel

        ↓ [Browse Rate: 40-70%]

Stage 2: PRODUCT ENGAGED (MoFU)
├── Definition: Views multiple products, reads reviews
├── Attribution: Linear
└── Key metric: Engaged sessions by channel

        ↓ [Add-to-Cart Rate: 8-15%]

Stage 3: CART (MoFU/BoFU transition)
├── Definition: Adds item to cart
├── Attribution: Time-decay (recency matters)
└── Key metric: Cart additions by channel

        ↓ [Cart Conversion: 30-70%]

Stage 4: PURCHASE (BoFU)
├── Definition: Completes checkout
├── Attribution: Last-touch
└── Key metric: Revenue, orders by channel
```

### E-commerce Metrics to Track

| Metric | Definition | Attribution Model |
|--------|------------|-------------------|
| **AOV** | Average order value | Last-touch |
| **Conversion rate** | Sessions → Purchases | Last-touch |
| **ROAS by channel** | Revenue / Ad spend | Full-funnel weighted |
| **New vs Repeat** | First purchase vs returning | First-touch (new), none (repeat) |
| **Purchase frequency** | Orders per customer/year | First-touch (sourcing) |

### E-commerce Forecast Formula

```ruby
# E-commerce Monthly Revenue Forecast
def ecommerce_monthly_forecast(channel)
  visitors = project_visitors(channel)               # From ToFU
  engaged = visitors * browse_rate(channel)          # 40-70%
  carts = engaged * add_to_cart_rate(channel)        # 8-15%
  purchases = carts * cart_conversion_rate(channel)  # 30-70%
  revenue = purchases * average_order_value          # AOV

  # Separate new vs repeat
  new_customers = purchases * new_customer_rate(channel)
  repeat_purchases = project_repeat_purchases        # From retention model

  {
    orders: purchases + repeat_purchases,
    new_customers: new_customers,
    revenue: revenue + (repeat_purchases * repeat_aov)
  }
end
```

### E-commerce Benchmark Rates

| Stage Transition | Low | Median | High |
|-----------------|-----|--------|------|
| Visitor → Engaged | 30% | 50% | 75% |
| Engaged → Cart | 5% | 10% | 20% |
| Cart → Purchase | 25% | 50% | 75% |
| **Overall Conversion** | 0.4% | 2.5% | 10% |

### E-commerce-Specific Considerations

**Repeat Purchase Layer:**

```ruby
# Layer repeat purchases on top of new customer forecast
def total_ecommerce_revenue(channel_forecasts)
  new_customer_revenue = channel_forecasts.sum { |c| c[:revenue] }

  # Repeat purchases from existing customers (not channel-attributed)
  repeat_revenue = existing_customers * repeat_rate * repeat_aov

  new_customer_revenue + repeat_revenue
end
```

