## Template 3: Marketplace (Two-Sided Platform)

### Dual Funnel Structure

Marketplaces must forecast **both sides** of the platform:

```
Marketplace Dual Funnel
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

SUPPLY SIDE (Sellers/Providers)          DEMAND SIDE (Buyers/Consumers)
═══════════════════════════════          ═══════════════════════════════

Stage 1: VISITOR (ToFU)                  Stage 1: VISITOR (ToFU)
├── Seller landing page                  ├── Buyer landing page
├── First-touch attribution              ├── First-touch attribution
└── Metric: Seller leads                 └── Metric: Buyer sessions

        ↓ [Signup: 5-15%]                        ↓ [Browse: 50-80%]

Stage 2: REGISTERED (MoFU)               Stage 2: ENGAGED (MoFU)
├── Creates seller account               ├── Views listings, searches
├── Linear attribution                   ├── Linear attribution
└── Metric: Registered sellers           └── Metric: Engaged buyers

        ↓ [List: 30-60%]                         ↓ [Intent: 10-25%]

Stage 3: ACTIVE SELLER (MoFU)            Stage 3: CART/BOOK (BoFU)
├── Lists first product/service          ├── Adds to cart or books
├── Participation attribution            ├── Time-decay attribution
└── Metric: Active listings              └── Metric: Cart adds/bookings

        ↓ [First Sale: 20-50%]                   ↓ [Convert: 40-70%]

Stage 4: TRANSACTING (BoFU)              Stage 4: PURCHASE (BoFU)
├── Completes first transaction          ├── Completes transaction
├── Last-touch attribution               ├── Last-touch attribution
└── Metric: GMV, take rate               └── Metric: GMV, orders
```

### Marketplace Metrics to Track

| Metric | Side | Attribution Model |
|--------|------|-------------------|
| **GMV** | Both | Split by demand-side last-touch |
| **Take rate** | Platform | N/A (business metric) |
| **Seller activation** | Supply | First-touch (sourcing) |
| **Liquidity** | Both | Ratio of supply/demand |
| **Repeat transaction rate** | Demand | First-touch |

### Marketplace Forecast Formula

```ruby
# Marketplace Forecast (must balance supply and demand)
def marketplace_forecast
  # Supply-side forecast
  seller_leads = project_seller_leads_by_channel
  registered = seller_leads * seller_signup_rate        # 5-15%
  active_sellers = registered * listing_rate            # 30-60%
  transacting = active_sellers * first_sale_rate        # 20-50%

  total_supply_capacity = transacting * avg_listings_per_seller

  # Demand-side forecast
  buyer_sessions = project_buyer_sessions_by_channel
  engaged = buyer_sessions * browse_rate                # 50-80%
  intent = engaged * intent_rate                        # 10-25%
  purchases = intent * conversion_rate                  # 40-70%

  # GMV limited by whichever side is constrained
  potential_gmv = purchases * average_order_value
  supply_limited_gmv = total_supply_capacity * avg_item_price

  actual_gmv = [potential_gmv, supply_limited_gmv].min
  platform_revenue = actual_gmv * take_rate

  {
    gmv: actual_gmv,
    revenue: platform_revenue,
    supply_utilization: actual_gmv / supply_limited_gmv,
    demand_conversion: purchases / buyer_sessions
  }
end
```

### Marketplace-Specific Considerations

**Supply-Demand Balance:**

| Ratio | Situation | Action |
|-------|-----------|--------|
| Supply >> Demand | Sellers underutilized | Invest in demand acquisition |
| Demand >> Supply | Buyers can't find inventory | Invest in seller acquisition |
| Balanced | Optimal state | Grow both proportionally |

**Attribution Complexity:**

- Demand-side revenue: Attribute normally (first/last/linear)
- Supply-side contribution: Harder to attribute—sellers enable transactions
- Recommendation: Attribute GMV to demand channels, but track seller sourcing separately

