## Template 4: B2B Lead Generation (Sales-Assisted)

### Funnel Structure

```
B2B Lead Gen Funnel
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

Stage 1: VISITOR (ToFU)
├── Definition: First website visit
├── Attribution: First-touch
├── Lookback: 60-90 days
└── Key metric: Traffic by channel

        ↓ [Lead Rate: 1-5%]

Stage 2: LEAD / MQL (MoFU)
├── Definition: Form fill, content download, demo request
├── Attribution: Linear
├── Lookback: 30-60 days
└── Key metric: MQLs by channel

        ↓ [Qualification Rate: 20-40%]

Stage 3: SQL / OPPORTUNITY (MoFU)
├── Definition: Sales-accepted, opportunity created
├── Attribution: Participation (all influences)
├── Lookback: 30 days
└── Key metric: SQLs, pipeline value

        ↓ [Win Rate: 15-35%]

Stage 4: CLOSED WON (BoFU)
├── Definition: Contract signed
├── Attribution: Last marketing touch (before sales)
├── Lookback: 14-30 days
└── Key metric: Closed revenue, deal count
```

### B2B Metrics to Track

| Metric | Definition | Attribution Model |
|--------|------------|-------------------|
| **Pipeline** | Total SQL value | First-touch (sourcing) |
| **Velocity** | Average days to close | By channel |
| **Win rate** | SQLs → Closed Won | Last marketing touch |
| **CAC** | Cost per closed deal | Full-funnel weighted |
| **ACV** | Average contract value | Last-touch |

### B2B Forecast Formula

```ruby
# B2B Lead Gen Forecast
def b2b_monthly_forecast(channel)
  visitors = project_visitors(channel)               # From ToFU
  mqls = visitors * lead_rate(channel)               # 1-5%
  sqls = mqls * qualification_rate(channel)          # 20-40%
  opportunities = sqls * opportunity_rate(channel)   # 60-80%
  closed = opportunities * win_rate(channel)         # 15-35%
  revenue = closed * average_contract_value          # ACV

  # Pipeline = opportunities not yet closed
  pipeline_value = opportunities * avg_deal_size

  {
    mqls: mqls,
    sqls: sqls,
    pipeline: pipeline_value,
    closed_deals: closed,
    revenue: revenue
  }
end
```

### B2B Benchmark Rates

| Stage Transition | Low | Median | High |
|-----------------|-----|--------|------|
| Visitor → MQL | 0.5% | 2% | 7% |
| MQL → SQL | 15% | 30% | 50% |
| SQL → Opportunity | 50% | 70% | 85% |
| Opportunity → Closed | 10% | 25% | 45% |
| **Overall Visitor → Closed** | 0.004% | 0.1% | 1.3% |

### B2B-Specific Considerations

**Sales Cycle Adjustment:**

```ruby
# B2B forecasts must account for pipeline timing
def b2b_forecast_with_timing(channel, forecast_month)
  # SQLs from 60-90 days ago will close this month
  sqls_closing = sqls_from_days_ago(channel, 60, 90)
  closes_this_month = sqls_closing * win_rate(channel)

  # SQLs generated this month will close in 2-3 months
  new_sqls = generate_new_sqls(channel, forecast_month)
  future_pipeline = new_sqls * avg_deal_size

  {
    this_month_revenue: closes_this_month * acv,
    pipeline_created: future_pipeline,
    expected_close_month: forecast_month + avg_sales_cycle_months
  }
end
```

**Marketing vs Sales Attribution:**

| Stage | Attributed To |
|-------|--------------|
| Visitor → MQL | Marketing (full credit) |
| MQL → SQL | Marketing + SDR (shared) |
| SQL → Opportunity | Sales (primary) |
| Opportunity → Closed | Sales (primary), marketing influence |

